(104, 'David Allen', 'd.allen@amdnewsdesk.com', '', 'US', 'We have a reporter that is doing an story and he may want to involve your business. I was looking for the correct contact person that may represent the company i an interview or just some questions.\r\n\r\nPlease note, this is not a reference to a solicitation of any services in any way shape or form. AMD News is one of the largest news coverage firms in the world if you are not already familiar with our firm. Please take a moment to investigate us utilizing the link below my signature that contains reputable organizations like the BBB, Yelp and so on, or as deep as you feel is necessary before replying to this email.\r\n\r\nIf you have not recently aired a commercial, and if we deem this is a fit for both parties, we would be creating and airing some TV commercial spots with any business message you would like to get out to the public to obtain research for our article about the effects and responses from TV commercials. Nothing goes out without your approval and you would have full input on the commercial as if you had hired a commercial production company, but without any expense to you whatsoever.\r\n\r\nIn exchange for the commercial production and airtime we are providing your only responsibility is to answer some questions after your commercials air. No strings whatsoever, only the interview and answers to our questions is what we require in exchange for the commercial production.\r\n\r\nWe are funded for projects such as these from our national news and publication wire service customers. It enables us to produce and air these commercials gratis for you to obtain our clean research data. This article will be on the national wire after it is all put together.\r\n\r\nJust to be very clear, all your commercial production and airtime is totally funded by our project and our clients if you do not already have a commercial that has recently aired. We do not require any financial obligation at all or information from you or your business, nor any future obligations at any time, but you must answer the questions after your commercials air as I mentioned. Again take a look at who we are as we know this can seem like an odd request. \r\n\r\nIt seems this is the only way we can obtain the clean data we require is to create the commercials ourselves if you have not recently aired a commercial.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know who I would contact in this regard, and what would be the best day and time to speak on the phone for a preliminary talk about this assignment before any interviews take place to see if it is a fit for both parties.\r\n\r\nThank you, and I look forward to hearing from you either way please.\r\n\r\nDavid Allen\r\nAssignment Desk 3b\r\nAMD News\r\nUS-Canada\r\n888-319-6336 ext 709 (by appointment only please)\r\nd.allen@amdnewsdesk.com\r\nhttp://www.americanmediad.com/main/aboutuslinks\r\n\r\nDirect BBB link:at http://www.bbb.org/new-jersey/business-reviews/news-service/american-media-distribution-in-howell-nj-90096055\r\n\r\n FYI, as a media firm we prefer to remain not accredited as may notice that other large media firms such as - US New and NY Times are not accredited as well.\r\n'),
